16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1911 of Title 25, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The State of Oklahoma hereby adopts the non-legally binding
21 Working Definition of Anti-Semitism adopted by the International
22 Holocaust Remembrance Alliance (IHRA) on May 26, 2016, including the
23 contemporary examples of anti-Semitism set forth therein,
24 exclusively as a tool and guide for training, education, and
